# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Pipeline run artifacts — regenerated by scripts on every pass.
# 01_data/ CSVs (notion_sources.csv, classifications.csv,
# classification_manifest.csv, by_concept/*.csv) are untracked ahead of making
# this repo public — they'll live in their own data repo and be pulled in at
# runtime. 02_logs/ is pure run history. 03_notion_drafts/ holds generated
# Notion content; regeneratable from notion_sources.csv via the
# per-folder/compact draft scripts.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
01_data/notion_sources.csv
01_data/classifications.csv
01_data/classification_manifest.csv
01_data/by_concept/
01_data/eval/
02_logs/
03_notion_drafts/

# URL-list artifacts in 00_inputs/. urls_dedup.csv is consumed by the pipeline
# (fetch.py, build_manifest.py) but stays out of the public repo — it lives in
# the separate data repo alongside the 01_data/ CSVs. The others are one-time
# outputs from manual URL curation. Listing each file explicitly so a future
# input file under 00_inputs/ isn't accidentally ignored.
00_inputs/urls.csv
00_inputs/urls_already_in_folder.csv
00_inputs/urls_dedup.csv
00_inputs/urls_filtered.csv
00_inputs/urls_not_in_folder.csv
00_inputs/urls_removed.csv

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Claude Code tool state — including spec docs, which are useful while
# building a feature but don't need to live in the repo long-term.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.claude/
CLAUDE.md

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Skill definitions — user-personal (hardcode local vault paths and are
# consumed by the user's Claude sessions, not by repo cloners).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
skills/

